==Transactions==
* June 26, 1999 – Drafted by the [[Vancouver Canucks]] in the first round, second overall, in the [[1999 NHL Entry Draft]]
* July 27, 1999 – Signed with the Canucks to a three-year contract&lt;ref name=contract99&gt;{{cite news|title=NHL Transactions – July 1999|url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/hockey/shn/shntr811.htm|accessdate=2008-09-25|date=1999-07-27|publisher=''[[USA Today]]''}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* July 29, 2003 – Re-signed with the Canucks to a one-year, $1.125 million contract&lt;ref name=contract03&gt;{{cite news|title=Sedin twins get raises, remain with Canucks|url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20030729&amp;slug=nhl29|accessdate=2008-09-25|publisher=''[[Seattle Times]]''|date=2003-07-29}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* September 10, 2004 – Re-signed with the Canucks to a one-year contract&lt;ref name=contract04&gt;{{cite news|title=Canucks re-up Sedins, Auld|url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/hockey/nhl/2004-09-10-roundup_x.htm|accessdate=2008-09-25|date=2004-09-10|publisher=''[[USA Today]]''}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* June 30, 2006 – Re-signed with the Canucks to a three-year, $10.75 million contract&lt;ref name=contract06&gt;{{cite news|title=Canucks secure Sedins|url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/british-columbia/story/2006/06/30/sedins-contract.html|accessdate=2008-09-25|date=2006-06-30|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Company]]}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* July 1, 2009 – Re-signed with the Canucks to a five-year, $30.5 million contract&lt;ref name=contract09/&gt;

